      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "74b7f54101c3e4a4",
      "text": "Let’s assume that the environment in which we live can be represented as some sort of space that looks like a [[vector space]]. It is a big assumption to make, but since we do not experience our environment directly, we do not have access to the true nature of the universe and as such the assumption cannot be disproven right away. As such, we will keep working under this premise as long as it helps us get to a more precise model of what we perceive. For naming purposes, we will refer to the vector space representation of the universe with the letter *U*.\n\n\n"
